## Proposed Changes

### Frontend Change Detection (Zoneless Support)

We will inject `ChangeDetectorRef` (CDR) and invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in all key components inside their asynchronous subscriptions (HTTP calls and SSE listeners).

#### [MODIFY] [register.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/auth/register/register.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `onRequestOtp()` (success and error) and `onSubmit()` (error callback).

#### [MODIFY] [login.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/auth/login/login.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `onRequestOtp()` (success and error) and `onSubmit()` (error callback).

#### [MODIFY] [technician-login.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/technician/login/technician-login.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `onSubmit()` (error callback).

#### [MODIFY] [profile.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/components/profile/profile.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `loadProfile()` (success), `loadOrders()` (success), and `saveProfile()` (success/error).

#### [MODIFY] [create-order.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/order/create-order/create-order.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `loadAvailableSlots()` (success/error), `getCurrentLocation()` (success/error callbacks), and `onSubmit()` (error callback).

#### [MODIFY] [navbar.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/components/navbar/navbar.ts)
* Inject `ChangeDetectorRef` in constructor.
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` in `refreshNewOrdersCount()` and inside the SSE `connect().subscribe` callback.

#### [MODIFY] [technician-dashboard.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/technician/dashboard/technician-dashboard.ts)
* Invoke `this.cdr.detectChanges()` inside the SSE `connect().subscribe` callback for both `order-available` and `order-accepted` events.

#### [MODIFY] [technician-orders.ts](file:///d:/Work/App/mobile-service/src/app/technician/orders/technician-orders.ts)
